&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*** Please note that NEL At-Risk candidates will be given priority consideration ***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are currently recruiting for a Payroll Associate to join our busy payroll team in Ashford Kent. This role is to deliver an effective and competent level of payroll support and to consistently deliver a high level of data accuracy to ensure confidence in payments made to staff with credible workforce data. To support the team with data input and any general HR and Payroll office support.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant must be able to deal with high volumes of work to meet tight deadlines and have an eye for detail to provide a high level of accuracy as well as be confident in Microsoft Office especially Outlook.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will initially require remote working until we return to the office so you will need to be able to manage your time, work on your own initiative and communicate effectively to a high standard with the team and our customers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further details on this role, please refer to the job description attached. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;****PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY****&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
